            <entry xml:id="entry_kom_2" n="2" xml:lang="os">
                <form type="lemma"><orth>kom</orth></form>
                <re>
                    <note type="comment" xml:lang="ru">в выражении</note>
                    <note type="comment" xml:lang="en">in the expression</note>
                    <form type="lemma"><orth>kom dæddyn</orth></form>
                    <sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>соглашаться</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>agree</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense>
                </re>
                <abv:exampleGrp>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>ældar yn læxstæ kæny, fælæ ḱyzg kom na dæddy</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>алдар умоляет ее, но девушка не дает согласия</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>Aldar is begging her, but the girl does not give consent</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_СОПам."/><biblScope>III
                            115</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>ranyxas-banyxas fækodtoj… æmæ bony fæstagmæ Farīzety fyd kom
                            radta</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>судили-рядили, и под конец отец Фаризет дал согласие (выдать
                                дочь)</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>they were hashing and and rehashing, and in the end father Farizet
                                agreed (to marry off his daughter)</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Čerm."
                            /><biblScope>131</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                </abv:exampleGrp>
                <etym xml:lang="ru">Восходит к иран. %i*kāma-%i ‘желание’: <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/>
                        <w>kām</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="pal"><lang/>
                        <w>kāmak</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="xcl"><lang/>
                        <note type="comment" xml:lang="ru">(из пехл.) </note><note type="comment"
                            xml:lang="en">(from Pahlavi) </note><w>kʼamk</w>
                        <gloss><q>желание</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="xcl"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>воля</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="xcl"
                            ><w>k’amim</w>
                        <gloss><q>я хочу</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sog"><lang/>
                        <w>*kām-(kʼm-)</w>
                        <gloss><q>хотеть</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sog"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>любить</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/>
                        <w>kama-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="peo"><lang/>
                        <w>kāma-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/>
                        <w>kāma-</w>
                        <gloss><q>желание</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>любовь</q></gloss></mentioned>. Сюда и глагол <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_komyn"/> ‘уступать’, ‘соглашаться’ q. v. — Выражение %ikommæ
                    kæsyn%i ‘повиноваться’, буквально „смотреть в рот“, связано не с этим, а с
                    предыдущим словом (<ref type="xr" target="#entry_kom"/>).%n<bibl><ref
                            type="bibl" target="#ref_Hübschmann._Oss."
                        /><biblScope>45</biblScope></bibl>.—-<bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."/><biblScope>20</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
                <etym xml:lang="en">It traces back to Iranian %i*kāma-%i ‘wish’: <mentioned
                        xml:lang="fa"><lang/>
                        <w>kām</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="pal"><lang/>
                        <w>kāmak</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="xcl"><lang/>
                        <note type="comment" xml:lang="ru">(из пехл.) </note><note type="comment"
                            xml:lang="en">(from Pahlavi) </note><w>kʼamk</w>
                        <gloss><q>wish</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="xcl"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>will</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="xcl"
                            ><w>k’amim</w>
                        <gloss><q>I want</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sog"><lang/>
                        <w>*kām-(kʼm-)</w>
                        <gloss><q>to want</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sog"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>to love</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/>
                        <w>kama-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="peo"><lang/>
                        <w>kāma-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/>
                        <w>kāma-</w>
                        <gloss><q>wish</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>love</q></gloss></mentioned>. It is related to a verb <ref
                        type="xr" target="#entry_komyn"/> ‘to give in’, ‘to agree’ q. v. — The
                    expression %ikommæ kæsyn%i ‘to obey’, literally „to look into the mouth“, is
                    connected not with this word, but with the previous one (<ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_kom"/>).%n<bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Hübschmann._Oss."
                            /><biblScope>45</biblScope></bibl>.—-<bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."/><biblScope>20</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
            </entry>
